# myctl

> My control tool.

A comprehensive CLI tool for managing resources.

## Global Options

- `-o, --output enum[text\|json\|yaml]` — Output format. (default: text)

## Commands

### myctl deploy

Deploy to environment.

Deploy the application to the specified target environment.

**Arguments:**

- `target` — Target environment. (required)

**Options:**

- `-f, --force` — Force deploy.
- `--count int64` — Instance count. (default: 1; required)
- `--endpoint string` — Deploy endpoint. (default: https://deploy.example.com; env: DEPLOY_ENDPOINT)

---

#### myctl deploy rollback

Rollback deployment.

**DEPRECATED**: Use 'deploy --rollback' instead.

---

